===Verb===
{{en-verb|dash|es}}

# {{intransitive}} To run [[quick]]ly or for a [[short]] distance.
#: ''He '''dashed''' across the field.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[leave]] or [[depart]].
#: ''I have to '''dash''' now. See you soon.''
# {{intransitive}} To [[destroy]] or [[ruin]].
#: ''He '''dashed''' the bottle against the bar and turned about to fight.''
# {{transitive}} To [[destroy]] by [[striking]] (against).
#: ''The glass was '''dashed''' during a fit of rage.''
# {{transitive}} To throw [[violent]]ly.
#: ''The man was '''dashed''' from the vehicle during the accident.''
# {{transitive}} To [[sprinkle]]; to [[splatter]].
# {{transitive}} To [[ruin]]; to [[destroy]].
#: ''Her hopes were '''dashed''' when she saw the damage.''
# {{transitive}} To [[dishearten]]; to [[sadden]].
#: ''Her thoughts were '''dashed''' to [[melancholy]].''
# {{transitive}} To complete hastily, usually with ''down'' or ''off''.
#: ''He '''dashed''' down his eggs'', ''she '''dashed''' off her homework''

